Comment: The carbon tax scheme initially adopted in BC (although it has been significantly undermined by later politically motivated scaling back) was effective.  

That model was marked by simplicity of taxation and tax revenue recycling back to BC residents highlighted by a moderate but predetermined and well-publicized legislated schedule of increases in the carbon tax rate (and therefore of rebates to Provincial residents). Consumers, manufacturers, and marketers, therefore, knew in advance that the rate of carbon taxation would increase in moderate (but significant in accumulation) set stages into the indefinite future.  

The cumulative effect of this scheme:   
• An incentive to reduce carbon based consumption at the time of each purchase;
  • Maintain the amount of money available for consumption in the Provincial economy;  
• Prompts development and marketing of products and technology that feature carbon emission reduction.

